\begin_layout Section
Problems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose a License plate must consist of 7 numbers of letter.
 How many license plates are there if
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
there can only be letters?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
the first three places are numbers and the last four are letters?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
the first three places are numbers and the last four are letters, but there
 can not be any repetitions in the same license plate?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A school of 50 students has awards for the top math, english, history and
 science student in the school
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways can these awards be given if each student can only win one
 award?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways can these awards be given if students can win multiple awards?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
An iPhone password can be made up of any 4 digit combination.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
How many different passwords are possible? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many are possible if all the digits are odd? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many can be made in which all digits are different or all digits are
 the same?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
There is a class of 25 people made up of 11 guys and 14 girls.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways are there to make a committee of 5 people?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways are there to pick a committee of all girls?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways are there to pick a committee of 3 girls and 2 guys?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If a student council contains 10 people, how many ways are there to elect
 a president, a vice president, and a 3 person prom committee from the group
 of 10 students?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose you are organizing your textbooks on a book shelf.
 You have three chemistry books, 5 math books, 2 history books and 3 english
 books.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways can you order the textbooks if you must have math books first,
 english books second, chemistry third, and history fourth?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
How many ways can you order the books if each subject must be ordered together?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
You buy a Powerball lottery ticket.
 You choose 5 numbers between 1 and 59 (picked on white balls) and one number
 between 1 and 35 (picked on a red ball).How many ways can you 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
win the jackpot (guess all the numbers correctly)? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
match all the white balls but not the red ball? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
match 3 white balls and the red ball?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
A couple wants to invite their friends to be in their wedding party.
 The groom has 8 possible groomsmen and the bride has 11 possible bridesmaids.
 The wedding party will consist of 5 groomsman and 5 bridesmaids.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
How many wedding party's are possible? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose that two of the possible groomsmen are feuding and will only accept
 an invitation if the other one is not going.
 How many wedding party's are possible? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose that two of the possible bridesmaids are feuding and will only accept
 an invitation if the other one is not going.
 How many wedding party's are possible? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose that one possible groosman and one possible woman refuse to serve
 together.
 How many wedding party's are possible? 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
There are 52 cards in a standard deck of playing cards.
 The poker hand is consists of five cards.
 How many poker hands are there?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
There are 30 people in a communications class.
 Each student must have a conversation with each student in the class for
 a project.
 How many total convesations will there be? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suppose a college basketball tournament consists of 64 teams playing head
 to head in a knockout style tournament.
 There are 6 rounds, the round of 64, round of 32, round of 16, round of
 8, the final four teams, and the finals.
 Suppose you are filling out a bracket such as this 
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename pics/1.1.png
	scale 20

\end_inset

which specifies which teams will win each game in each round.
 How many possible brackets can you make? 
\end_layout

